content.description: Up ramp to arete, past pin and 2 bolts then make transition from right wall to left wall and go past 2 more bolts to the top.
content.protection: A fixed pin then 4 bolts. No anchors.
content.location: 10' right of Chunks at the far right end of white wall. To the right of the cave.

content.description: Start below the arete across from the fin at the entrance to White Wall. Follow arete and cracks to top.
content.location: The obvious arete on your left as you exit the narrow corridor heading to White Wall from the Iceberg Area.

content.description: start about 10' left of the obvious right facing corner of Wayne's Woute. Follow the cracks.
content.location: Between the corner and Wayne's Woute.

content.description: Through small roof to ledge and layback flake. When flake runs out, traverse right past bolt, then easier terrain to top. Skip the crux by going right from ledge 10' below bolt (maybe 5.6?) FA did main route left of bolt,straight up face and easy ramp right of bolt. Not sure about left offshoot near top.
content.protection: Standard rack. One bolt. old coldshuts.
content.location: start to the left of tree.

content.description: Boulder up flake to into hole then follow pitons up small cracks to small roof. Step right and finish on Chunks, cracks to top.
content.location: Same start as Chunks. Up flake left of cave into hole. On the right end of White wall.

content.description: Boulder to left-facing flake. layback this till it ends. Crank up and right, then step back left toward bolt then crank to top.
content.location: Between Birth Canal and Chunks, below left facing flaring flake. Behind small tree.

content.description: Stay left of the Unnamed Arete by climbing the easy slab to the crux at the small roof.  After the crux follow easy terrain to the top.
content.protection: No bolts, No anchors.  Top of the arete's crack accepts C4 2# for a top rope.
content.location: Just left of the Unnamed Arete 5.10.

content.description: Boulder up into hole then step left and crank up right facing flake to small roof. Traverse right and pull bulge then climb crack to top.
content.location: Begins to the left of cave.

content.description: Begin 10' left of Birth Canal and head for the small roof and mantle onto the ledge. Figure out how to get off the ledge and head up and left then trend right to easier ground.
content.location: Between Wayne's route and Birth Canal. A couple feet to right of tree and above the little thorn bush.

content.description: Climb through obvious slot and be born again to the ledge, then follow nice finger crack to top.
content.location: to right of large tree. bouldery start below obvious slot, or start 8' to right and traverse up to slot (easier). Tree anchor (be nice to tree) or walk down.

content.description: Start a couple feet left of Groove machine and climb the face past a bolt.
content.location: Right of Birth Canal. Left of Groove machine. Below the single bolt.
